"&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nWritten evidence from\n \nCyclox\n \n(CYS0130)\n&#xa0;\nThe following was submitted via the committee's website online application form, if I've missed anything, I'm sure it will be covered by one of the numerous other \nknowledgeable submissions\n&#xa0;\nThis is the submission by \nCyclox\n of Oxford, for measures that would help safer cycling.   It covers cycle training, enforcement of regulations, infrastructure and planning.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nPlanning requirements for cycle parking provision at residential/business developm\nents are enforced. For people to feel able to use their bikes, they need to be confident there will be a secure parking place at their destination to help prevent theft of their cycle. One quarter of those who have a cycle stolen give up cycling and don't \nreplace their cycle.\n&#xa0;\nJanuary 2014\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n"